Coding Questions

Q1. Write a Java program to serialize an object of a class and save it to a file.

Q2. Write a Java program to deserialize an object from a file and print its field values.

Q3. Write a Java program to demonstrate the effect of the transient keyword—serialize and deserialize an object, showing that transient fields are not saved.

Q4. Write a Java program where a parent class is serializable but the subclass is prevented from being serialized.
